ize it or not. →\" [ref=e34] [cursor=pointer]:\n        - /url: /modules/module-1\n        - generic [ref=e35]: \"1\"\n        - generic [ref=e36]:\n          - generic [ref=e37]:\n            - heading \"What AI Actually Is\" [level=3] [ref=e38]\n            - generic [ref=e39]: 30 min\n            - generic [ref=e40]: +200 XP\n          - paragraph [ref=e41]: Cut through the hype and understand what's really going on\n          - paragraph [ref=e42]: In 4 short lessons, you'll learn what AI actually does (vs. what the marketing says), why it's different from regular software, how the models behind ChatGPT work, and where AI is already changing your daily life — whether you realize it or not.\n        - generic [ref=e43]: →\n      - link \"2 The Vocabulary 40 min +250 XP The tech terms that actually matter — explained like you're a smart adult APIs, CLIs, LLMs, MCPs, tokens, context windows, fine-tuning. These words get thrown around constantly. In 5 lessons you'll actually understand what they mean — with real-world analogies, no jargon, and interactive exercises to make them stick. →\" [ref=e44] [cursor=pointer]:\n        - /url: /modules/module-2\n        - generic [ref=e45]: \"2\"\n        - generic [ref=e46]:\n          - generic [ref=e47]:\n            - heading \"The Vocabulary\" [level=3] [ref=e48]\n            - generic [ref=e49]: 40 min\n            - generic [ref=e50]: +250 XP\n          - paragraph [ref=e51]: The tech terms that actually matter — explained like you're a smart adult\n          - paragraph [ref=e52]: APIs, CLIs, LLMs, MCPs, tokens, context windows, fine-tuning. These words get thrown around constantly. In 5 lessons you'll actually understand what they mean — with real-world analogies, no jargon, and interactive exercises to make them stick.\n        - generic [ref=e53]: →\n      - link \"3 AI in Your Day 32 min +240 XP Real workflows. Real time savings. No code required. Stop reading about AI and start using it. In 4 practical lessons, you'll see exactly how AI handles email, scheduling, customer service, and data analysis — with before/after comparisons showing the actual time you'll get back. Each lesson is one use case, explained start to finish. →\" [ref=e54] [cursor=pointer]:\n        - /url: /modules/module-3\n        - generic [ref=e55]: \"3\"\n        - generic [ref=e56]:\n          - generic [ref=e57]:\n            - heading \"AI in Your Day\" [level=3] [ref=e58]\n            - generic [ref=e59]: 32 min\n            - generic [ref=e60]: +240 XP\n          - paragraph [ref=e61]: Real workflows. Real time savings. No code required.\n          - paragraph [ref=e62]: Stop reading about AI and start using it. In 4 practical lessons, you'll see exactly how AI handles email, scheduling, customer service, and data analysis — with before/after comparisons showing the actual time you'll get back. Each lesson is one use case, explained start to finish.\n        - generic [ref=e63]: →\n      - link \"4 Security, Privacy, and Trust 32 min +200 XP What you actually need to know before you trust an AI tool In 4 lessons, you'll learn what prompt injection is and why it matters, what happens to your data when you use AI tools, how to spot vendor lock-in before it traps you, and how to evaluate whether an AI tool is actually trustworthy. No fear-mongering — just honest, practical information. →\" [ref=e64] [cursor=pointer]:\n        - /url: /modules/module-4\n        - generic [ref=e65]: \"4\"\n        - generic [ref=e66]:\n          - generic [ref=e67]:\n            - heading \"Security, Privacy, and Trust\" [level=3] [ref=e68]\n            - generic [ref=e69]: 32 min\n            - generic [ref=e70]: +200 XP\n          - paragraph [ref=e71]: What you actually need to know before you trust an AI tool\n          - paragraph [ref=e72]: In 4 lessons, you'll learn what prompt injection is and why it matters, what happens to your data when you use AI tools, how to spot vendor lock-in before it traps you, and how to evaluate whether an AI tool is actually trustworthy. No fear-mongering — just honest, practical information.\n        - generic [ref=e73]: →\n      - link \"5 Evaluating AI Tools and Vendors 32 min +200 XP Make smarter buying decisions before you spend a dollar In 4 lessons, you'll learn how to decide if you actually need AI (or just better processes), how to spot the red flags in vendor sales pitches, what questions to ask before buying anything, and how AI pricing models work — plus a clear framework for deciding whether to build, buy, or wait. →\" [ref=e74] [cursor=pointer]:\n        - /url: /modules/module-5\n        - generic [ref=e75]: \"5\"\n        - generic [ref=e76]:\n          - generic [ref=e77]:\n            - heading \"Evaluating AI Tools and Vendors\" [level=3] [ref=e78]\n            - generic [ref=e79]: 32 min\n            - generic [ref=e80]: +200 XP\n          - paragraph [ref=e81]: Make smarter buying decisions before you spend a dollar\n          - paragraph [ref=e82]: In 4 lessons, you'll learn how to decide if you actually need AI (or just better processes), how to spot the red flags in vendor sales pitches, what questions to ask before buying anything, and how AI pricing models work — plus a clear framework for deciding whether to build, buy, or wait.\n        - generic [ref=e83]: →\n      - link \"6 Your First AI Implementation 32 min +200 XP Stop planning. Start doing. Here's your 2-week blueprint. In 4 lessons, you'll learn how to pick the right first AI project, set honest expectations with the people involved, measure whether it's actually working, and avoid the mistakes that kill 80% of first implementations. You'll finish with a concrete action plan you can use immediately. →\" [ref=e84] [cursor=pointer]:\n        - /url: /modules/module-6\n        - generic [ref=e85]: \"6\"\n        - generic [ref=e86]:\n          - generic [ref=e87]:\n            - heading \"Your First AI Implementation\" [level=3] [ref=e88]\n            - generic