ef=e36]: Show it millions of dog photos → it learns to recognize dogs\n          - listitem [ref=e37]: Show it billions of sentences → it learns to predict what word comes next\n          - listitem [ref=e38]: Show it thousands of X-rays → it learns to spot abnormalities\n        - paragraph [ref=e39]:\n          - strong [ref=e40]: There is no \"thinking\" happening.\n          - text: There's no understanding, no feelings, no consciousness. AI is extraordinarily good at finding patterns humans would miss — but it has no idea what those patterns\n          - emphasis [ref=e41]: mean\n          - text: .\n        - separator [ref=e42]\n        - heading \"The Marketing vs. The Reality\" [level=2] [ref=e43]\n        - button \"? AI is intelligent ▼\" [ref=e44] [cursor=pointer]:\n          - generic [ref=e45]:\n            - generic [ref=e46]:\n              - generic [ref=e47]: \"?\"\n              - generic [ref=e48]: AI is intelligent\n            - generic [ref=e49]: ▼\n        - button \"? AI understands you ▼\" [ref=e50] [cursor=pointer]:\n          - generic [ref=e51]:\n            - generic [ref=e52]:\n              - generic [ref=e53]: \"?\"\n              - generic [ref=e54]: AI understands you\n            - generic [ref=e55]: ▼\n        - button \"? AI will take over ▼\" [ref=e56] [cursor=pointer]:\n          - generic [ref=e57]:\n            - generic [ref=e58]:\n              - generic [ref=e59]: \"?\"\n              - generic [ref=e60]: AI will take over\n            - generic [ref=e61]: ▼\n        - paragraph [ref=e62]: Click each card to see the reality behind the hype.\n        - separator [ref=e63]\n        - heading \"Why This Matters for You\" [level=2] [ref=e64]\n        - paragraph [ref=e65]: \"If you understand what AI actually is — a pattern-matching engine — you can:\"\n        - list [ref=e66]:\n          - listitem [ref=e67]:\n            - strong [ref=e68]: Use it intelligently\n            - text: instead of trusting it blindly\n          - listitem [ref=e69]:\n            - strong [ref=e70]: Spot bad vendor pitches\n            - text: \"(red flags: \\\"fully autonomous,\\\" \\\"no human needed\\\")\"\n          - listitem [ref=e71]:\n            - strong [ref=e72]: Set realistic expectations\n            - text: about what AI can and can't do\n          - listitem [ref=e73]:\n            - strong [ref=e74]: Stay ahead\n            - text: of people who bought the hype and got burned\n        - paragraph [ref=e75]: The people winning with AI right now aren't the ones who think it's magic. They're the ones who understand its limits.\n        - separator [ref=e76]\n        - heading \"Quick Check\" [level=2] [ref=e77]\n        - generic [ref=e78]:\n          - generic [ref=e80]: 🎯 Quick Check\n          - generic [ref=e81]:\n            - generic [ref=e82]:\n              - paragraph [ref=e83]: 1. At its core, what does AI actually do?\n              - generic [ref=e84]:\n                - radio \"Thinks independently, like a human brain\" [ref=e85] [cursor=pointer]:\n                  - generic [ref=e87]: Thinks independently, like a human brain\n                - radio \"Finds patterns in data to make predictions\" [ref=e88] [cursor=pointer]:\n                  - generic [ref=e90]: Finds patterns in data to make predictions\n                - radio \"Stores and retrieves information, like a database\" [ref=e91] [cursor=pointer]:\n                  - generic [ref=e93]: Stores and retrieves information, like a database\n                - radio \"Writes its own code to improve itself\" [ref=e94] [cursor=pointer]:\n                  - generic [ref=e96]: Writes its own code to improve itself\n            - generic [ref=e97]:\n              - paragraph [ref=e98]: 2. Which statement about AI is TRUE?\n              - generic [ref=e99]:\n                - radio \"AI understands the meaning behind what you write\" [ref=e100] [cursor=pointer]:\n                  - generic [ref=e102]: AI understands the meani